               . The Wald statistics andp‐values for this test are presented in row e oftable 5, and the data failed to support the null at all usual levels of significance. These results indicate the presence of possible reverse nonlinear causality and imply that the Suominen (2001) model describes only part of the price‐volume relationship. While information about volume may assist in forecasting returns uncertainty, it is also the case that information about returns is useful in forecasting the conditional variance of volume. Any empirical model that imposes the assumption of one‐way nonlinear causality on Hong Kong price‐volume data would be misspecified and could potentially yield unreliable inference and forecasts

