               , ∀m,non the estimates of(17), and the results are presented in row f oftable 5. These Wald test results confirm the presence of asymmetric response in the variance‐covariance structure to news about volume and volatility. On balance, the asymmetry would appear to be a function of asymmetric responses to unanticipated returns. In terms of returns volatility, we find strong evidence of own‐variance asymmetry. The conditional volatility of volume and the conditional covariance between volume and returns are also found to respond asymmetrically to return innovations.

